    "name": "KOKO HOTEL Osaka Umeda",
    "detail": "Location and nearby: The hotel very close to the Osaka station, take South gate walk through Hankyo department store. It is not far as expected when you found the shortcut direction through department stores. There are several department stores near the hotel and you can find Lawson,7-11 or Japanese restaurants next to and opposite the hotel. Many night clubs and bars surrounded the hotel, make sure not to walk pass through the sub road if you go with kids. Room: It is not easy to find the large room in Osaka. You may found difficulty when open your large luggages please be noted that not only this hotel but many hotels are mostly the same size in Osaka. For me I’ve been stayed here for 3 nights (90% of my Osaka trip) since it is located in the good location and easy to find late dinner at night. Staff: Nice and friendly, you can leave your luggages before check in time (03:00 PM.) Overall: I would suggest this hotel to the travelers but it depend on your life style too if you feel not comfort to stay in the town crowded, many night clubs, close to the main road— so this hotel is not your answer. For me, I will stay in this hotel again for my next Osaka trip.",
